Hi Phil, I ran into the exact same problem. Alternatively, you can use connect-mongo version 4 by slightly modifying Zach's code, in which the connection is not established through mongoose, but is directly with MongoStore.create in the in app.use(session) invocation.
The code goes like this:
const MongoStore = require('connect-mongo'); // The post version 4 does not accept (session) here.
// dbString and dbOptions are not modifed

app.use(session({
    secret: process.env.SECRET,
    resave: false,
    saveUninitialized: true,
    store: MongoStore.create({
        mongoUrl: dbString,
        mongoOptions: dbOptions,
        collectionName: 'sessions'
    }),
    cookie: {
        maxAge: 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24 // Equals 1 day (1 day * 24 hr/1 day * 60 min/1 hr * 60 sec/1 min * 1000 ms / 1 sec)
    }
}));

This works fine, the only problem is that you have to create another connection with mongoose to create the User model, but this doesn't seem to conflict. If someone has a better solution, it's more than welcomed...

